title: PATIKIL Glowing Stones, 300 Pcs Glow in the Dark Rocks for Indoor Outdoor Fish Tank Decorations Garden Yard Landscaping Gifts for Friends, Orange Yellow
features: Specification: Color: Orange Yellow Material: Long Afterglow Phosphor of Rare Earth, Polystyrene Resin Size: 15 - 20 × 15 - 20 mm / 0.59 - 0.79 × 0.59 - 0.79 Inch (L ×W ) Packing List: One bag contains 100 pieces

Advantage: The Glowing Stones are made of good materials, durable and non-radioactive, and pose no harm to humans and animals. They are reusable, emitting a long-lasting glow, and can be used in various settings such as gardens, fish tanks, and indoor spaces.

Application: The glowing stones can be used in gardens, placed along trails or in flower beds to add a magical touch and create a beautiful and enchanting atmosphere at night. In fish tanks and aquariums, they provide an interesting look and enhance the aesthetic appeal. Additionally, they can also be used as decorative elements on shelves, in vases, in potted plants or as part of table centerpieces in indoor spaces.s, in vases, in potted plants or as part of table centerpieces in indoor spaces.

Instruction: Place them on a flat plane without stacking. Charge by putting them under sunlight or bright LED light for 10 - 15 minutes. Use them right after charging and they can glow in the dark for more than 10 hours. Recharge when needed.

NOTE: 1. If the glowing stones charged for only 5 minutes or less, or have been left outside for a while and might have started glowing and losing energy before sunset, a dim glow at night is normal. 2. Don't leave the glowing stones under light with the package. 3. When the stones are glowing, please make sure the surroundings are dark enough.
